			<section>
				<h3>Roman fractions</h3>
				<p>Roman fractions work in a similar way to whole numbers: to create a =
fraction you need to arrange symbols in the order of descending value in su=
ch a way so that they sum up to the number you want to represent. There are=
 14 symbols that can be used to create fractions. They are listed in the ta=
ble below.</p>
